article.description: — Antonio Rizzuto had 17 points and Kellon Taylor added 16 to lead Albany over UMass Lowell 81-69 on Saturday.
article.headline: Albany defeats UMass Lowell 81-69
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- — Antonio Rizzuto had 17 points and Kellon Taylor added 16 to lead Albany over UMass Lowell 81-69 on Saturday. Jamel Horton had 14 points and five steals and Cameron Healy scored 10 points for Albany (5-7, 5-5 America East Conference). Kalil Thomas had 19 points for the River Hawks (8-10, 7-7). Allin Blunt added 11 points. Connor Withers had nine rebounds. The Great Danes evened the season series against the River Hawks with the win. UMass Lowell defeated Albany 79-71 on Friday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
